  "text": "RT-qPCR results indicated late amplification of some plant miRNA, but the quality of data was low and inconsistent with specific, reliable detection. Strikingly, despite consistent and efficient plant miRNA amplification from material corresponding to sub-nanoliter volumes of the plant miRNA source to 35 PCR cycles, results of RT-qPCR reactions for plasma were highly variable. Many reactions did not amplify, and standard deviations for amplifying replicates were high. We aim generally for Cq standard deviations of 0.2 or less for our miRNA assays; for all but the miR160 reactions, standard deviations (to the extent they could be calculated) were generally greater than 1. miR172 most abundant canonical miRNAs, but sequencing approaches [CITATION_1] and carefully controlled labeling experiments could provide answers.",
